System Requirements:
====================

2 GB of Space on your harddisk

RapidEnv currently basically works under Windows and Linux.
It has been tested so far with:
- Windows XP
- OpenSUSE Linux 11.4

A Java Runtime Environment (Version 1.6.x) has to be
installed in order to run the RapidEnv command line tool "renv".


To do:
======

- Open a Windows command prompt or Unix shell or terminal window
  in folder RapidEnvExampleJavaEE/environment/bin

- start RapidEnv by entering command:

  - Windows> renv -yes

  - Linux>   . renv -yes
             Prepending . is essential to influence the
             environment settings of the current shell window.

    On Linux additional interactions might be neccessary because
    the JDK installation / deinstallation requires root user
    rights.
